Identify the primary signal type from this list:
- buyback_authorization: Company announces share repurchase program
- ceo_change: CEO, President, or C-suite departure or appointment
- earnings_release: Quarterly or annual earnings results
- ma_announcement: Merger, acquisition, or divestiture announcement
- debt_issuance: New debt facility, bond issuance, or credit agreement
- restatement: Financial restatement or accounting correction
- material_contract: Significant new customer, supplier, or partnership contract
- other: None of the above

For sentiment, assess whether the event is:
- positive: Clearly good for shareholders (buyback, strong earnings, major contract win)
- negative: Clearly bad for shareholders (restatement, CEO fired, debt increase)
- neutral: Informational or ambiguous

Rate relevance_score from 0.0 to 1.0:
- 1.0: Immediately actionable for a fundamental investor (CEO change, buyback, restatement)
- 0.7–0.9: Important context (earnings beat, major contract)
- 0.4–0.6: Moderate relevance (routine debt facility, minor management change)
- 0.0–0.3: Low relevance (routine compliance filing, minor update)

